Key Match Events: Marcel Sabitzer scored the winning goal for Austria with a spectacular angled finish.
Donyell Malen scored an own goal to give Austria an early lead.
Romano Schmid scored for Austria with a diving header.
Memphis Depay equalized for the Netherlands after a VAR review overturned a handball decision.
Cody Gakpo scored for the Netherlands after a 60-yard run by Xavi Simons.
Post-Match Reflections: Ralf Rangnick praised his team's energy and performance.
Ronald Koeman expressed regret over the Netherlands' poor opening spell.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Austria topped Group D, with the Netherlands finishing third.
Austria will face the runners-up from Group F in the knockout stage.
Patrick Wimmer will miss the next round due to a booking.
